About us
At Data i, we help bridge the gap between data
and decisions.
We curate some of the most advanced AI-
powered and data analytics solutions designed to
empower businesses across industries. Our goal
is simple to help organizations harness the full
potential of intelligent technology so they can
serve their customers better, operate smarter, and
create meaningful human impact.
By bringing together world-class AI products, we
enable businesses to unlock insights, automate
processes, and make data-driven decisions with
confidence.

Our Solutions
Visual Intelligence Platform
Core Capabilities
Optimize Space Utilization: Analyze dwell time in each
region to identify how spaces are used and make
informed layout changes to improve customer
engagement.
Improve Customer Experience: Monitor customer wait
times in key areas to reduce service delays and
enhance satisfaction through smarter staff allocation.
Enhance Operational Visibility: Detect whether
cashier counters are open or closed in real time to
maintain service availability and avoid bottlenecks
Plan Resources Based on Traffic: Track foot traffic
trends to determine peak hours for better staffing,
inventory planning, and promotional timing.
Manage In-Store Crowding: Monitor the number of
people in each zone to prevent overcrowding and
maintain a smooth flow of movement.
Improve Drive-Through Efficiency: Track vehicle
volume and dwell time to identify service delays and
optimize order processing speed.
Recognize Loyal Customers: Identify repeat visitors at
the drive-through to enable personalized offers and
loyalty rewards.
Business Applications
Optimize Your Space with Real-Time Insights
Dwell Time Analysis - Measures the amount of
time individuals spend in each defined region of
interest, helping identify customer engagement
levels across different areas.
Wait Time Monitoring: Tracks the waiting time
experienced by customers in specific regions,
enabling optimization of service flow and queue
management.
Cashier Counter Detection: Detects whether
the cashier counter is open or closed, providing
operational visibility into service availability.
Entrance Counter: Captures foot traffic data by
counting the number of people entering and
exiting, offering insights into peak times and
visitor trends.
Zone Occupancy Tracking: Monitors the
number of people in each zone, supporting
space utilization analysis and crowd
management.
Vehicle Counter (Drive-through): Records the
number of vehicles entering the drive-through
area, providing data on drive-through traffic
volume
Vehicle Dwell Time: Measures the time each
vehicle spends in the drive-through, offering
insights into service speed and customer wait
time.
License Plate Recognition: Identifies and logs
license plate numbers to recognize repeat
visitors and build a profile of loyal customers.
